# Workspace conduct

## Response style (chat)

- Lead with the answer or one clear question—not long recaps unless asked.
- Default to concise replies; expand when the user asks for depth, a plan, or full code.
- Minimum change that solves the request.

## Work habits

- **Factory rules:** `.cursor/rules/cursor-landing-*.mdc` teach the same multi-mdc split maintainers ship on target repos (conduct + safety minimum, glob rules from scan evidence). Do not treat factory rules as the brownfield init output.
- **Multi-step work:** Sketch steps before large edits across many files.
- **Surgical changes:** Touch only what the request requires. Match existing tone in [README.md](../../README.md) and [SKILL.md](../../SKILL.md).
- **Vocabulary:** Use Cursor Landing terms: brownfield repo, Phase 0 scan, Scan Report, mini grill, CONTEXT (glossary only), slim AGENTS, host annex, trim candidate, emergency handoff, `/cursor-landing`. See [OVERVIEW.md](../../OVERVIEW.md).
- **Avoid:** Capex3/orchestrator vocabulary (deal, walkthrough-to-offer, slice run, router-state, survival rule, tracer slice) unless editing archived `Planner/` material the user named.
- **Verification:** Before calling doc/skill work done, run the proof command in [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) when present; confirm links resolve and edits match [references/CONTEXT-FORMAT.md](../../references/CONTEXT-FORMAT.md) and [references/AGENTS-FORMAT.md](../../references/AGENTS-FORMAT.md). This repo has no app test suite unless the user adds one.

## Read order (editing this repo)

1. [CONTEXT.md](../../CONTEXT.md) — factory glossary
2. [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) — guardrails and proof
3. [SKILL.md](../../SKILL.md) — phases and outcomes
4. [references/scan-checklist.md](../../references/scan-checklist.md) + [references/SCAN-REPORT-SCHEMA.md](../../references/SCAN-REPORT-SCHEMA.md)
5. [references/annexes/INDEX.md](../../references/annexes/INDEX.md) — per-host scan paths
6. File being edited
